Routeable endpoints.
The routeable origins and destinations.

Arrays with the expanded endpoints (from m_allOrigs and m_allDests). This must be routeable items, that means that the IDs might only refer to street segment items.

    The routeable origins.

Endpoints

    The origin in the caluclated route.
  • origDestFinalPoint_t m_destPoint

Detailed Description

Send route-request to the Route Module.

Before that both coordinates and IDs for the origins and destinations must be looked up.

Member Enumeration Documentation

enum RouteObject::state_t [private]
 

The possible states of this object.

Enumeration values:
AWAITING_ORIGDEST  Awaiting entering of origins and destintions.

The request is not yet handled to the server.

ROUTINGINFO  RoutingInfo is retreived.
SENDING_ITEM_EXPAND  Sending RouteItemExpandRequestPackets or CoordinateRequestPackets to the map module.
RECEIVING_ITEM_EXPAND  Waiting for RouteItemExpandReplyPackets or CoordinateReplyPackets from the map module.
SENDING_ROUTE  Sending the route-request packet to the route module.
RECEIVING_ROUTE  Waiting for the route-reply packet from the route module.
SENDING_EXPAND_ROUTE  Sending the ExpandRouteRequestPackets to the map module.

Let the ExpandRouteObject do the actual work.

RECEIVING_EXPAND_ROUTE  Wait for expand route reply packet.

The packets are handled direct to the RouteExpander.

SENDING_NAME_REQUEST  Send ItemNamesRequestPackets to the map module.
RECEIVING_NAME_REQUEST  Wait for ItemNamesReplyPackets from the map module.
DONE  All processing completed.
ERROR  Something whent wrong when processing any part of the task for this object.

uint32 RouteObject::calcNbrWantedRoutes (  uint32  nbrWantedResults  )  [private]
 

Calculates the number of routes to tell the RouteSender to calculate to be able to return the specified number of routes.

The number is calculated by taking the nbrWantedResults destinations which expand to the largest number of SSI:s and sum the number of SSI:s for them. The value is then multiplied with 2, since we use both node0 and node1.

Parameters:
nbrWantedResults The final wanted number of results.
Returns:
The number of routes to calculate.
